    <briefdescription>
<para>Software timer service — one-shot and periodic timers. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Timers are caller-owned structs with a callback. They can be used with or without the scheduler. In a bare main loop, call <ref refid="syn__timer_8h_1a0c0174789e236228d039a30d29bfe95d" kindref="member">syn_timer_service()</ref> each iteration. With the scheduler, run it from a high-priority task.</para>
<para>Timers are driven by <ref refid="syn__port__system_8h_1a6c7d98587814b2c0d9c09da02d318873" kindref="member">syn_port_get_tick_ms()</ref> — resolution depends on how often you call <ref refid="syn__timer_8h_1a0c0174789e236228d039a30d29bfe95d" kindref="member">syn_timer_service()</ref>.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keyword">static</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/><ref refid="structSYN__Timer" kindref="compound">SYN_Timer</ref><sp/>heartbeat;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">void</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>on_heartbeat(<ref refid="structSYN__Timer" kindref="compound">SYN_Timer</ref><sp/>*t,<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keywordtype">void</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>*ctx)<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><ref refid="syn__gpio_8h_1a5fb76e41e0f60e4a24fe304a89baef04" kindref="member">syn_gpio_toggle</ref>(LED_PIN);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__timer_8c_1af77b4cb799d5a240b851a5b74a1712d6" kindref="member">syn_timer_init</ref>(&amp;heartbeat,<sp/>1000,<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">true</highlight><highlight class="normal">,<sp/>on_heartbeat,<sp/>NULL);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__timer_8c_1afe28882f9f48c2fc3f0cdc063a525662" kindref="member">syn_timer_start</ref>(&amp;heartbeat);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="keywordflow">while</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>(1)<sp/>{</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><sp/><sp/><sp/><sp/><ref refid="syn__timer_8c_1a0c0174789e236228d039a30d29bfe95d" kindref="member">syn_timer_service</ref>(&amp;heartbeat,<sp/>1);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">}</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
